83. Develop a PHP script to accept email addresses and validate it. Display the domain name of the
email and result of validation.
code:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Email Validation</title>
</head>
<body>
<h2>Email Validation Form</h2>

<form method="post" action="">
    Enter Email: <input type="email" name="email" required>
    <input type="submit" name="submit" value="Validate">
</form>

<?php
if(isset($_POST['submit'])) {
    $email = $_POST['email'];

    // Validate email using filter_var
    if(filter_var($email, FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL)) {
        $valid = "Valid Email";
        
        // Extract domain
        $domain = substr(strrchr($email, "@"), 1); // gets string after '@'

        echo "<p style='color:green;'>$valid</p>";
        echo "<p>Domain Name: <strong>$domain</strong></p>";
    } else {
        echo "<p style='color:red;'>Invalid Email!</p>";
    }
}
?>
</body>
</html>
